    "summary": "Carlo Klein  is an experienced people manager and certified project manager in the RF telecommunications, semiconductor, photonics and automotive industry.\n\nHe received the MSc degree in Electrical Engineering in 1992 from the University of Twente on IC-technology and Electronics.\n\nFrom 1992 until 2001, he worked for Ericsson as RF and system engineer on DECT, Bluetooth and UMTS. From 2001 until 2002, he joined Agere Systems as system architect working on WLAN Radio Backbone Systems.\n\nFrom 2002 until 2005 he was responsible as project manager for CMOS radio transceiver ICs with National Semiconductor in the Netherlands (ao. LMX4168 product family). \n\nIn 2005 he joined NXP Semiconductors and was responsible for FM Radio ICs from conception to mass production (ao. TEA5760 product family), receiving NXP\u2019s Excellence Award in the category Product Creation. Since then, he has played several roles as department manager and project management consultant.\n\nIn 2014, he joined Amazon as Product Development Manager and Manager of the Design and Engineering team. Carlo holds a US Patent on Electrowetting displays.\n\nIn 2016, he joined Philips Photonics Modules as Integral Project Manager, responsible for a number of laser sensor development projects.\n\nIn 2018, he joined EFFECT Photonics as Engineering Director, responsible for the development and release of highly integrated optical communications products.\n\nIn 2020, he joined Qorvo as Project Manager, responsible for the development and release of integrated IoT controllers (ao. QPG7015M product family).\n\nKeywords:\nPeople management, project management, product development, RF, PMP, WiFi, WLAN, W-CDMA, UMTS, Bluetooth, DECT, Automotive, CMMi, semiconductor, photonics, test development, mass production, production flow, quality management, risk management, configuration management, engineering,  ASIC, RFIC, PIC, BiCMOS, CMOS, TFT arrays, electrowetting, VCSEL, laser, characterisation, networking, application, analogue, mixed signal, amplifier, low-noise, high-density, microwave, PLL, DSP, FPGA, SoC, electrical engineering, electronics, software, hardware, firmware, design, R&D. Pragmatic , no-nonsense, humour, can-do.",
